
Output a sorted list of files by the number of hits a grep search retuns


grep -P: use perl regex
grep -c: output counts instead of the lines that match.

sort -k: which field to sort on
sort -t: what to use as a field delimeter
sort -n: compare numerical values instead of string values

grep -Pc $SEARCH_REGEX $FILES | sort -t ":" -k 2 -n
